[2018-06-24 22:36] elyot: @Drevoed Sentinel was just kinda designed as this generic protective unit and we debated between husks and engineers and eventually just went with engineer because it enabled more combos. It's a case of spike winning over melvin/vorthos.

@mrguy888 Yeah the urban sentries don't cost gaussite in the story, but it's implied that some robots might still use gaussite power cells for fuel

@ZzZombo Prismata on Linux is web-only because Adobe doesn't support Stage3D in the Linux version of AIR so we don't have any GPU-accelerated graphics and it runs like shit.

@Miccull If you want to boost people's position on the ladder then that would not be allowed. If you just want to get accounts to higher levels then we wouldn't care. 

@UndefeatedOrca Megabrawl was just an event with some slightly-altered parameters. Community members can't really run them.

@Deleted User Campaign all missions done, cutscenes done but still editing, art/etc. 90% done, testing still ongoing. We'll enable public testing in the next few days we think.

@MrNewt Avatars broke for a brief period on saturday because a cat accidentally stepped on the keyboard while we were adding some new custom avatars.

@jonshea Yes, buying from the website gives a code that you can share/send to somebody

@cactus well, you might just be bad. In theory every Prismata set is a theoretical win for p1 or p2 (or a draw), but in practice even the very best players seldom play the best strategy, especially when they're just seeing a set for the first time (and there are almost always lines for both players that challenge/complicate the position). If you think Perforator is too good for one side or the other, you probably just need to try more things (e.g. turn 2 animus)
